        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/{size}/43780_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-18T12:13:55.122Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Flare is not an official Signal app and is an entirely third party tool developed by someone else. If you aren’t willing to use the Signal Desktop flatpak you definitely shouldn’t use Flare. The Signal Desktop flatpak at least uses the official Signal code; it is just being repackaged by a third party.</p>\n<p>The Signal team only officially supports Debian based Linux because they are small and don’t have the capacity to test and troubleshoot issues from other distros, so they just say it’s not supported and don’t publish packages for anything else so they don’t give the impression that it is.</p>\n<p>However, it does work well on most distros. I personally use the flatpak on Fedora.</p>",
