        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"esharota\" data-post=\"8\" data-topic=\"70485\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/9dc877/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> esharota:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>for flare app you have blue tick</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Yes, but all that means is that the developer whose name is on it has verified that they are indeed the developer. So you can be certain that Julian Schmidhuber is the developer who is publishing Flare on flathub, but that tells you nothing about his trustworthiness or the security of his code, and it does not mean it’s an official Signal app.</p>\n<p>More details about verified apps:</p><aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://docs.flathub.org/docs/for-users/verification\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://docs.flathub.org/img/favicon.svg\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"16\" height=\"16\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://docs.flathub.org/docs/for-users/verification\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">docs.flathub.org</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/459;\"><img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/optimized/3X/9/a/9a56c06973195ae703b6a0def7e771d71e518907_2_690x459.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" data-dominant-color=\"3C8BE5\" width=\"690\" height=\"459\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://docs.flathub.org/docs/for-users/verification\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Verified apps | Flathub Documentation</a></h3>\n\n  <p>What is a verified app?</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>Signal on flathub is <em>not</em> verified because it’s not actually being published there by the Signal Foundation; someone else is doing it on their behalf.</p>",
